    "Language acquisition is a subconscious process, and learners are unaware of the process underway.",
    "Once new knowledge is acquired, learners actually don't realize they possess that knowledge.",
    "This is analogous to how children learn their native language.",
    "Language learning involves formal instruction and therefore is a conscious process.",
    "New language forms are represented and may consciously be compared by learners as \"rules\" and \"grammar.\""
